        B12 | THE STRAITS TIMES TUESDAY, AUGUST 18, 2020 | | | OBITUARIES "I know that You can do all things, And that no thought or purpose of Yours can be restrained." Job 42:2 “The Lord is my shepherd, He leads me beside still waters, He restores my soul.” 3rd Anniversar­y In Loving Memory Of Psalm 23 Chow Kok Wing Age: 56 (1964 - 2020) was called home to be with the Lord on 16 August 2020 CHIAM CHENG CHUAN LIM WEE KIEN Mother: Age: 91 Departed on 18 August 2017 Mdm Lim Kam Neo was called home to be with the Lord on 17 August 2020, dearly missed by loved ones. Sister: Chow May Lin Husband: Tan Fong Hoe ( ) ✟ He had a smile, a pleasant way, A helping hand to all he knew, He was kind, generous and true, On earth he nobly did his best; Grant him, heavenly rest. Brothers: Sister-in-Law: Sons: Chow Kok Yang Amy Ong Chow Kok Qong (deceased) James Tan Kiat Min ( ) Richard Tan Hong Chiew ✟ Daughters: Thank you for your thoughts and prayers. There will not be any wake or nightly services. Cremation was on 17th Aug 2020 Serena Tan Lan Foon Tan Lan Fang Deeply missed and always remembered by Brothers, Sister, Nephews, Nieces and all loved ones Daughter-in-law, sons-in-law, grandchild­ren, granddaugh­ter-in-law, great granddaugh­ter, relatives and friends. Wake is held at Blk 521 Ang Mo Kio Ave 5 S(560521). Hp: 9030 0630 Nightly services will be held from 18 Aug 2020 at 8.00pm. Cortege will leave on 19 Aug 2020 ( Wed) at 6.00pm for Mandai Crematoriu­m Hall 2 for cremation at 6.45pm. (From L to R) Darren Cheng, CEO • Jenny Tay, MD • Roland Tay, Founder obituaries online Find today’s Death announceme­nts in The Straits Times are now digitised to make it easier for the deceased’s next-of-kin to share news of the demise of their loved one. Find the online version of the obituaries published today at : or
